**Implementation**: Metodos en `PdfDocument<R>` que delegan a `crate::ai::export_to_markdown(self)`, etc.

### Step 2.3 -- `chunk()` convenience method

```
TEST: test_chunk_basic
- chunks = doc.chunk(512)
- Assert Ok, non-empty, cada chunk tiene content

TEST: test_chunk_small_size
- chunks con chunk(10) tiene mas chunks que chunk(512)

TEST: test_chunk_respects_size
- chunks = doc.chunk(50)
- Assert todos los chunks tienen tokens <= 60 (tolerancia)

TEST: test_chunk_with_overlap
- chunks = doc.chunk_with(ChunkConfig { size: 100, overlap: 20 })
- Assert overlap entre chunks consecutivos
```

**Implementation**:
```rust
pub fn chunk(&self, target_tokens: usize) -> ParseResult<Vec<DocumentChunk>> {
    let chunker = DocumentChunker::new(target_tokens, target_tokens / 10);
    let extracted = self.extract_text()?;
    let page_texts: Vec<(usize, String)> = extracted.iter().enumerate()
        .map(|(i, t)| (i + 1, t.text.clone())).collect();
    chunker.chunk_text_with_pages(&page_texts).map_err(...)
}
```

**Files**:
- MODIFY: `oxidize-pdf-core/src/parser/document.rs` (add open, to_markdown, to_contextual, to_json, chunk, chunk_with)
- CREATE: `oxidize-pdf-core/tests/vibecoding_facade_test.rs`

