### Step 3.7 -- PdfDocument::partition()

```
TEST: test_pdfdocument_partition
- doc = PdfDocument::open(fixture con tablas y headers)
- elements = doc.partition()
- Assert non-empty, al menos un Paragraph

TEST: test_pdfdocument_partition_with_config
- elements = doc.partition_with(PartitionConfig::new().without_tables())
- Assert no Table elements

TEST: test_partition_preserves_page_numbers
- Multi-page doc
- Assert elements tienen page numbers correctos

TEST: test_partition_reading_order
- Elements en reading order (pagina por pagina, top to bottom)
```

**Implementation**:
- `pipeline::partition::Partitioner` con `partition(fragments, config) -> Vec<Element>`
- Internamente: 1) Detectar headers/footers por posicion, 2) Detectar tablas via StructuredDataDetector, 3) Detectar KV pairs, 4) Detectar titulos por font-size ratio, 5) Detectar listas por prefijos bullet/number, 6) Resto = Paragraph
- `PdfDocument::partition()` y `partition_with(config)` delegan a Partitioner

**Files**:
- CREATE: `oxidize-pdf-core/src/pipeline/partition.rs`
- MODIFY: `oxidize-pdf-core/src/pipeline/mod.rs`
- MODIFY: `oxidize-pdf-core/src/parser/document.rs` (add partition(), partition_with())
- CREATE: `oxidize-pdf-core/tests/partition_test.rs`

